 at z<0.4 than at 1.5<z<3.6, which\nresults in median and mean b-values that are 15-30% higher at low z than at\nhigh z. The ratio of the number density of BLAs to NLAs at z<0.4 is a factor of\n\\~3 higher than at 1.5<z<3.6.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 11 Dec 2006 17:32:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-11"}
